OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FGreenland's Inuits seek    
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25FDenmark compensation over  
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5Ffailed social experiment   
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Six indigenous Greenlanders taken as   
OL,6, children to Denmark in a failed social 
OL,7, experiment in 1951 are demanding       
OL,8, compensation from the Danish state.    
OL,10,FThe Inuits, now in their 70s, are the  
OL,11,Fsurviving members of the group of 22   
OL,12,Fchildren who were removed from their   
OL,13,Fhomes to be educated as "little Danes".
OL,15,FWhen they later returned to Greenland, 
OL,16,Fthey were put in an orphanage, and many
OL,17,Fdid not see their families again.      
OL,19,FThe six survivors each want #28,200    
OL,20,F($37,800), their lawyer says.          
OL,23,D]G     From the BBC News Website       
